Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:08 a.m. in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 26.25, or 0.6
percent, to 4,305.12.  Miners:  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nationâ€™s biggest
metals producer, led a decline among mining companies after
copper futures fell the most in seven weeks and  gold prices 
retreated. Philex sank 2.7 percent to 17.40 pesos, heading for
the sharpest loss since Feb. 28.  Atlas Consolidated Mining &
Development (AT)  Corp slipped 1.9 percent to 15.80 pesos.  Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  , owner of operator
of the longest Philippine toll road, dropped 3.1 percent to 3.77
pesos, set for the sharpest loss since March 29. The company
said it received notice that Metro Pacific Holdings Inc. will
exercise its right to swap 6.6 billion pesos ($152 million) of
convertible bonds into 2.03 billion shares of the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
